:''See also:'' [[gypsy]]
==English==

===Etymology===
From Old English[[category:Old English derivations]] [[Gypcyan]] < French[[category:French derivations]] [[gyptien]] (meaning [[Egyptian]]) < Latin[[Category:Latin derivations]] [[Aegyptius]]. See [[Egyptian]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|Gypsy|Gypsies}}

# A [[Rom]], member of the [[Roma]]. This term is considered pejorative by many and by the Roma themselves.
# One of a [[stateless]] people, whose communities, traditionally thought to have originally from India, entered Europe in 14th or 15th century, and are now widely distributed over Europe, Russia, Turkey, the Americas.
# The language of the [[Roma]] people.

